OL,3,CNumber of smokers drops by 10%, but
OL,4,Cprevalence 'remains high among
OL,5,Cvulnerable'
OL,7,FThe number of smokers in Northern
OL,8,FIreland has dropped from a quarter of
OL,9,Fthe population to 14%, but concern
OL,10,Fremains around prevalence among the
OL,11,Fmost vulnerable.JThe Auditor General
OL,12,FDorinnia Carville also expressed
OL,13,Fconcern at a rise in the numbers who
OL,14,Fvape ` from 5% to 9% of adults in the
OL,15,Flast 10 years, and an estimated 9% of
OL,16,F11 to 16-year-olds as well as 24% of
OL,17,FYear 12 students.JThe report, Tackling
OL,18,Fthe Public Health Impacts of Smoking
OL,19,Fand Vaping, records that an estimated
OL,20,F320,000 people aged 16 and over
OL,21,Fcurrently smoke in Northern Ireland.
