OL,7,FThis is around 14% and has dropped
OL,8,Ffrom 24% in 2010-11.JHowever, Ms
OL,9,FCarville's report finds that
OL,10,Fchallenges remain, particularly with
OL,11,Fsmoking prevalence significantly
OL,12,Fhigher among the most deprived areas `
OL,13,F24% compared to the least deprived at
OL,14,F7%.JIt was also found that around
OL,15,F2,200 pregnant women continue to smoke
OL,16,Fannually, and emerging research
OL,17,Fsuggests a high smoking prevalence
OL,18,Famongst people with mental health
OL,19,Fissues.JIn terms of impact on the
OL,20,Fhealth service, the report finds that
OL,21,Faround 15% of deaths in Northern
OL,22,FIreland (2,200) are attributable to
OL,23,Fsmoking, as are around 35,000 smoking-
OL,24,Frelated hospital admissions each year
OL,25,Fand an estimated #218 million spent on
OL,26,Ftreating smoking-related illnesses.
